docs.abstract: President Trump’s abrupt decision to pull forces from northern Syria forced the Pentagon to press ahead with a risky night operation that killed the ISIS leader, military officials said.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s abrupt decision to pull forces from northern Syria forced the Pentagon to press ahead with a risky night operation that killed the ISIS leader, military officials said.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump knew the Central Intelligence Agency and Special Operations commandos were zeroing in on the location for Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi, the Islamic State leader, when he ordered American troops to withdraw from northern Syria earlier this month, intelligence, military and counterterrorism officials said on Sunday.

headline.main: Trump’s Syria Troop Withdrawal Complicated Plans for al-Baghdadi Raid

docs.abstract: The president said the dog was chasing Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi in a darkened tunnel and was hurt when a suicide vest was detonated.
docs.snippet: The president said the dog was chasing Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi in a darkened tunnel and was hurt when a suicide vest was detonated.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The last moments of Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi’s life were spent being chased down a dark underground tunnel by military dogs. The dogs that sprinted after him, President Trump said about the Islamic State leader’s death on Sunday, were only deterred by a suicide bomb that detonated inside Mr. al-Baghdadi’s vest, killing him and several children.

headline.main: Trump Says ‘Beautiful’ and ‘Talented’ Dog Injured in al-Baghdadi Raid
headline.print_headline: ‘Talented’ K-9 Was Injured In Blast Caused by Vest

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Greg Walden of Oregon, a senior Republican on an influential House committee, said on Monday that he would not seek re-election, joining the growing ranks of Republicans rushing for the exits as they take stock of a grim political landscape ahead of the 2020 election.

docs.abstract: A text exchange given to Congress as impeachment investigators questioned their first witness shows an internal dispute over whether the president was seeking a quid pro quo from Ukraine.
docs.snippet: A text exchange given to Congress as impeachment investigators questioned their first witness shows an internal dispute over whether the president was seeking a quid pro quo from Ukraine.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A top American diplomat in Ukraine repeatedly raised concerns with colleagues about the White House’s decision to withhold $391 million in security aid from Ukraine, describing it as a “crazy” plan to withhold security assistance “for help with a political campaign,” according to texts released Thursday as part of the impeachment inquiry into President Trump.

docs.abstract: Representative Elijah E. Cummings, who died last week, became the first African-American elected official to lie in state in the Capitol on Thursday.
docs.snippet: Representative Elijah E. Cummings, who died last week, became the first African-American elected official to lie in state in the Capitol on Thursday.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Elijah E. Cummings, the powerful Democrat whose booming baritone and impassioned cries for decency reverberated through the halls of Congress for more than two decades, made history one final time on Thursday, as the first African-American elected official to lie in state in the United States Capitol.

headline.main: Making Capitol History, Cummings Is Remembered as a ‘Master of the House’
headline.print_headline: Lying in State, Cummings Breaks One Last Racial Barrier

docs.abstract: Republicans have railed against the secretive nature of the House impeachment inquiry, but that is typical of congressional investigations.
docs.snippet: Republicans have railed against the secretive nature of the House impeachment inquiry, but that is typical of congressional investigations.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Republicans’ move to occupy the secure chambers of the House Intelligence Committee on Wednesday may not have succeeded in shutting down Democrats’ impeachment inquiry. But for a day at least, it shifted debate in the Capitol away from damaging testimony against President Trump to questions about how the inquiry itself is being conducted.

headline.main: Why Is Democrats’ Impeachment Inquiry Out of Public View?
headline.print_headline: An Inquiry Is Out of Public View, but That’s Not Out of the Ordinary
